# Keywording for the baked desktop stack (see specs/installcd-stage1.spec).
# Only genuinely unkeyworded (9999-only) ebuilds get `**`; that is noctalia
# alone. niri, wlsunset and xwayland-satellite all ship a proper ~amd64 RELEASE
# in GURU, so they take `~amd64` -- NOT `**`. Using `**` on niri/wlsunset picked
# their 9999 live (git-r3) ebuild, which needs an offline git seed we don't have
# (only noctalia is in git-sources.conf) and dies at src_unpack. The newer
# main-tree Wayland tools are ~amd64 on this stable profile. NOTE: the first bake
# build may surface additional ~amd64 transitive deps to add here.
gui-shells/noctalia **
gui-wm/niri ~amd64
gui-apps/xwayland-satellite ~amd64
gui-apps/wlsunset ~amd64
gui-apps/foot ~amd64
gui-apps/wl-clipboard ~amd64

# Transitive ~amd64 deps surfaced by the bake (expected on a first desktop pass).
dev-cpp/sdbus-c++ ~amd64  # noctalia
